    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-03T10:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-31T17:07:00-05:00" n="360"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3791: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="52" xml:id="d360fn52">Repeated to the Commission to Negotiate Peace as
                        Department’s no. 629, Feb. 8, 2 p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-02-03T10:15:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1919-02-01T03:00:00+04:53">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received February 3, 1919, 10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                <p>“76. February 1, 3 a.m.</p>
                <p>On January 29th <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> took oath of
                    office before the Senate in Omsk and solemnly declared that the high power
                    conferred upon him by the Council of Ministers would be relinquished to the
                    All-Russian Government which would be created by a properly constituted
                    constituent assembly. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
